108. conprecatam opportuit. Ussing remarks that esse is invariably omitted. Langen corrects him, p. 54, quoting Trin. 1092, Most. 1093, Bacch. 819, Cas. 4. l. 83 but neither Ussing nor Langen notices that in all the passages they quote the verb is passive.
